  "text": "Depth image upsampling is a quite challenging task. Specifically, due to the limited spatial resolution, the LR image loses or distorts fine structures of the HR image. A brute-force upscaling method often makes those structures which have sharp edges become blurred in the upsampled image. In particular, for the case of single-image upscaling, the severely distorted fine structures often exist [CITATION_1] .",
